EXACT DERIVATION OF Q_1/ΣQ LIMIT
============================================================

THEOREM: For Interval tournament C_p^{1..m} with m=(p-1)/2:

  Q_1 = 1/(4·sin²(π/(2p)))

Proof: Let x = π/p. Then
  sin(mπ/p) = sin((p-1)π/(2p)) = sin(π/2 - x/2) = cos(x/2)
  sin(π/p)  = sin(x) = 2·sin(x/2)·cos(x/2)

  Q_1 = cos²(x/2) / sin²(x)
       = cos²(x/2) / [4·sin²(x/2)·cos²(x/2)]
       = 1 / [4·sin²(x/2)]
       = 1 / [4·sin²(π/(2p))]   □

Verification:
  p=   7: Q1_direct = 5.04891734, formula = 5.04891734, match = True
  p=  11: Q1_direct = 12.34353752, formula = 12.34353752, match = True
  p=  13: Q1_direct = 17.20685727, formula = 17.20685727, match = True
  p=  17: Q1_direct = 29.36529789, formula = 29.36529789, match = True
  p=  23: Q1_direct = 53.68231728, formula = 53.68231728, match = True
  p=  97: Q1_direct = 953.41435459, formula = 953.41435459, match = True
  p= 197: Q1_direct = 3932.25715037, formula = 3932.25715037, match = True
  p= 499: Q1_direct = 25229.15938162, formula = 25229.15938162, match = True
  p= 997: Q1_direct = 100714.25176451, formula = 100714.25176451, match = True

COROLLARY: Q_1/ΣQ = 2 / [(p²-1)·sin²(π/(2p))]

  Since ΣQ = m(m+1)/2 = (p²-1)/8,
  Q_1/ΣQ = [1/(4sin²(π/(2p)))] / [(p²-1)/8]
         = 2 / [(p²-1)·sin²(π/(2p))]

LIMIT (PROVED):
  Q_1/ΣQ → 8/π² = 0.810569469139 as p → ∞

Proof: sin(π/(2p)) = π/(2p) - O(p⁻³)
  sin²(π/(2p)) = π²/(4p²) · (1 - π²/(12p²) + O(p⁻⁴))
  (p²-1)·sin²(π/(2p)) = π²/4 · (1-1/p²)(1-π²/(12p²)+...) → π²/4
  Q_1/ΣQ = 2/(π²/4) = 8/π²  □

ASYMPTOTIC EXPANSION:
  Q_1/ΣQ = 8/π² + 8(12+π²)/(12π²) · p⁻² + O(p⁻⁴)
  = 0.8105694691 + 1.4772361358/p² + O(p⁻⁴)

Verification of asymptotic expansion (should be O(p⁻⁴) residual):
  p=   7: exact-8/π² = 3.09e-02, (exact-8/π²)·p² = 1.514921 (expect 1.477236), O(p⁻⁴) residual·p⁴ = 1.8466
